                  <summary>Will I own my website when it is done? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">100%. Once the project is complete and paid for, everything is yours — code, content, domain, and hosting account. No lock-in, no platform fees owed to us.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Do I need to sort out hosting and a domain myself? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">We handle the full setup for you. We recommend the right hosting for your site type, configure everything, and connect your domain. You do not need to touch any of it unless you want to.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Can I update the website myself after launch? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Yes. We hand you a short walkthrough showing how to make common changes yourself. And for anything else, your first year of maintenance is on us.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Are there any extra costs for tools or plugins? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">We normally build without locking you into specific paid tools. However, some projects require premium plugins or third-party add-ons to deliver a feature you specifically need — such as a booking system or payment gateway. In those cases the cost of those tools is covered by the client and will always be communicated clearly before we proceed.</p>
                </details>
              </div>

              <!-- Panel 4: Pricing & Payment -->
              <div id="faqpanel4" class="faq-panel">
                <details class="faq-item" open>
                  <summary>How much does a website cost? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                 <p class="faq-answer">Our projects start at $1,500 for landing pages, $2,500 for static business websites, and $3,500 for e-commerce stores. Final pricing depends on the number of pages, custom features, integrations, and your specific requirements. We provide a clear, itemized quote after your free strategy call — so you know exactly what you are paying for before committing to anything.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>How does payment work? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">We split the project into three payments: 50% upfront to start the project, 25% before we enter the final phase, and 25% on launch day after all final touches are complete.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Are there any ongoing costs after launch? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">The only recurring costs are hosting and your domain name — both of which you control directly. We cover maintenance, security updates, and small content edits one at a time free for your first 12 months.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Do you offer payment plans for larger projects? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">For projects of $2,000 and above we offer a structured payment plan using the same 50/25/25 split, making it easier to manage the investment as the project progresses.</p>
                </details>
              </div>

              <!-- Panel 5: AI & How We Build -->
              <div id="faqpanel5" class="faq-panel">
                <details class="faq-item" open>
                  <summary>Do you use AI in your web design process? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Yes — and it is one of the reasons we work faster and smarter than traditional agencies. We use AI tools across design, content structure, code generation, and SEO to accelerate every stage of the build without cutting corners on quality. You get the speed of AI with the judgment and strategy of a human team behind every decision.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Does AI mean my website will look generic? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Not at all. AI handles the repetitive and technical work — we handle the strategy, creative direction, and everything that makes your brand unique. Every website is custom to your business, AI just helps us get there faster.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Will my website be future-proof with AI search? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Yes. We build every site with clean structure, schema markup, and content architecture that performs in both traditional Google search and AI-powered search platforms like ChatGPT and Perplexity. As search evolves, your site is already built for what comes next.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Can you build AI features into my website? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Absolutely. We can integrate AI-powered chat, lead qualification tools, smart booking systems, and automated follow-up flows. If you have a specific idea, bring it to your strategy call and we will tell you exactly what is possible.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Why not use AI or Wix instead? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">You can build a site with AI in an afternoon. It'll look fine. It won't convert. AI generates websites; it doesn't generate customers. What AI can't do: research your specific local market, write copy that speaks to your specific customer's fear, structure the page so one CTA is the only obvious next step, or set up local SEO to actually rank in Cary or Durham. That's the work. The build is the easy part.</p>
                </details>
              </div>

              <!-- Panel 6: Results & Support -->
              <div id="faqpanel6" class="faq-panel">
                <details class="faq-item" open>
                  <summary>Will my website actually bring in new clients? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">That is the entire point of how we build. Every layout, call to action, and page structure is designed around conversion — not just aesthetics. Results depend on your market and traffic, but your site will be built to convert from day one.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>What is included in the 1 year of free maintenance? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Security monitoring, performance updates, and small content edits — one at a time — at no charge. If something breaks, we fix it. No ticket queues, no hourly billing.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>What happens after the first year? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">We offer affordable monthly maintenance plans. No obligation — you are free to manage it yourself or work with anyone else after year one.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>What if I need new pages or features after launch? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Small updates are covered under maintenance. Larger additions such as new service pages or features are quoted separately at a fair rate with no pressure.</p>
                </details>
                <details class="faq-item">
                  <summary>Why should I choose AK Digital House over a bigger agency? <span class="faq-icon"></span></summary>
                  <p class="faq-answer">Because you will not get passed to a junior account manager and forgotten. You work directly with us, get a faster launch, a more personal service, and a partner who grows alongside your business — not an agency that moves on once the invoice is paid.</p>
